    "16510835927f249308": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "1651083592c8987272-0": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Plastic Can't Simply Be Thrown Out",
            "use_h1": false
          }
        },
        "1651083592c8987272-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>According to Science Advances, 75% of all plastic produced since 1907 has been discarded, but only 9% has been recycled, with 12% being incinerated.<\/p><p>As plastic has an average life cycle of over 500 years, we now have over 5 billion metric tons of plastic clogging up coastlines, creating huge piles in the oceans, accumulating in cities, and taking over landfills. Unfortunately, it is projected that within the next decade alone, plastic production is expected to grow by 40%. <\/p>",
            "enlarge_text": false
          }
        },
        "e03afdc8-20ea-4f9b-908b-64b4bd4da950": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><em>Source: “<\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/www.science.org\/doi\/10.1126\/sciadv.1700782\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><em>Production, Use, and Fate Of All Plastics Ever Made.<\/em><\/span><\/a><em>” Science Advances. 19, July 2017<\/em><\/p>",
            "enlarge_text": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "1651083592c8987272-0",
        "1651083592c8987272-1",
        "e03afdc8-20ea-4f9b-908b-64b4bd4da950"
      ],
      "settings": {
